        print("I'am gamana from "bangalore"") -invalid
        print('''I'am gamana from "bangalore"''') - invalid
        print("I'am gamana form\"bangalore\"") - valid

More About Strings:
    1.String Slicing
        - excrating some part of a string.
        - Index starts from 0 , end index end-1 or len-1.or n-1 (where n is length of string).
        eg: s="kodnest"
            print(s) #kodnest
            print(s(start:stop:step))
            print(s[5])
            print(s[2:5])
            print(s[:4])
            print(s[2:])
            print(s[1:5:2])
            print(s[::2])
            print(s[1::])

        Negative indexing : from right to left : -1,-2,-3,-4...
            print(s[-2])
            print(s[-7:-2])
            print(s[:-1])
            print(s[-5:-1])
            print(s[::-1])
            print(s[-6::-2])
            print(s[-3:-8:-2])

